Italian police have released video footage of a crash between a light aircraft and a helicopter in the Alps in January. The crash, which took place near the Rutor glacier in the Aosta Valley, killed seven people. The footage was captured on a GoP camera which had been filming at the time of the accident but survived. It was later found after the snow had melted. Video reveals final steps of Himalayan climbers A video showing the final moments of eight international climbers killed in an avalanche in May is released by India's Indo-Tibetan Border Police.